"Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":41,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":50,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Gouvis II was born in 1174, in Dorset, England, his father, Robert de Gouvis, was 25 and his mother, Alice Gouls, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Robert de Gouvis II. He died in 1251, in Yorkshire, England, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1174–1251":"1174–1251","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1174–Female":"1174–Surnud","1190–1264":"1190–1264","1149–1229":"1149–1229","1149–1195":"1149–1195","1190":"1190","12 Sep 1229":"19. september 1229","1215":"1215","1149":"1149","1224":"1224","1264":"1264","1174":"1174","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","Abt 1190":"umbes 1190","1229":"1229","Dewlish, Dorset, England":"Dewlish, Dorset, England","North Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fi":{"1174–1251":"1174–1251","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1174–Female":"1174–Kuollut","1190–1264":"1190–1264","1149–1229":"1149–1229","1149–1195":"1149–1195","1190":"1190","12 Sep 1229":"19. syyskuuta 1229","1215":"1215","1149":"1149","1224":"1224","1264":"1264","1174":"1174","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","Abt 1190":"noin 1190","1229":"1229","Dewlish, Dorset, England":"Dewlish, Dorset, England","North Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fr":{"1174–1251":"1174–1251","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1174–Female":"1174–Décédée","1190–1264":"1190–1264","1149–1229":"1149–1229","1149–1195":"1149–1195","1190":"1190","12 Sep 1229":"19 septembre 1229","1215":"1215","1149":"1149","1224":"1224","1264":"1264","1174":"1174","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","Abt 1190":"environ 1190","1229":"1229","Dewlish, Dorset, England":"Dewlish, Dorset, Angleterre","North Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Dorset, England":"Dorset, Angleterre